main event: A civilian observed a domed-shaped object in Hyattsville, Maryland on February 16, 1965.
interesting points: The object was solid and sharply outlined at first before it gradually faded away,The observation was made in clear conditions with a bright day and clear sky,The object was estimated to be about 10-15 feet in diameter,It was observed descending at a speed of 800-900 mph from a distance of about 300 ft, The conclusion in the report suggested it was likely a conventional aircraft but did not adequately convince of its traditional identity.
sighted object: a domed-shaped object in the sky
witness description: A civilian without any specific training in astronomy or physics, but familiar with various types of aircraft due to former experience as a B-29 navigator.
